CatDescriptText: Mrs. Margaret Wilkes, 307 Thirty Fourth Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 28, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "What do you think is wrong with the Pittsburgh Pirates? Do you think that they are using their best ball players at all times?" answer reads: "They don't do it all the time, but they should have a free hand to arrest the big shot as well as the little, but as I say, it looks like they don't do it all the time."
